  "description": [
    "WHERE CHILDREN WORK THEY ARE BEING RECKED PHYSICAL LY AVP MENTALLY BY TWELVE HOURS LABOR A DAY IN MILLS DECLARES MRS MACFADTEN Mrs Macfadyen better known in this country as Irere Ashby sailed for England last week after a winter spent in the South working for legisla tion against child labor As Miss Ashby Mrs Macfadyen began this work under the auspices of the Federated Labor organi sations in the winter of 1901 Returning to Eng land last June she was married in September to Mr Macfadyen who is private secretary to the Prime Minister of Cspe Colony She returned to Alabama by request of a central committee or ganized by many of the most prominent and repre sentative people of the State for the purpose of securing legislation for he protection of the chil dren of the State The bill in South Carolina failed by only three votes The bill In Alabama went further than any previous bill had done It had a public hearing before the legislative committee which attracted wide attention and was reported favorably to the legislature where however it was not permitted to come to a vote In Kentucky the bill passed forbidding the employment"
